last_episode_to_air.name: Mustangs Forever and Ever
last_episode_to_air.overview: The Mustangs have to face whether the team has a future, and Lara realises she has something important to tell Ruby.

name: Mustangs FC
overview: A goal kicking comedy drama about girls who are abandoning the sidelines and starting their local football club’s first all-female team. Against the odds, they’ll stand united and overcome any challenge the club, the boys or the opposition can throw at them, all while wrestling with what it means to be a girl today.

episodes.name: Goals
episodes.overview: It's the beginning of the season for brand new all-girl soccer team, Mustangs, and football tragic Marnie can't wait to get started. But with no coach, no uniforms and no players - can Marnie pull a team together?

episodes.name: Like A Boss
episodes.overview: When the Mustangs get accused of 'playing like girls', it's the last straw for Marnie. It's time to prove themselves by beating the boys. So they challenge them to a golden goal game.

episodes.name: Can't Even
episodes.overview: Liv and Marnie fall out and when Liv turns to new team superstar, Ruby, for reassurance, Marnie loses it. Ruby is totally stealing her best friend as well as her position on the team.

episodes.name: Game Changer
episodes.overview: Lara is driving Marnie crazy and totally invading her space. But when Marnie posts an unflattering pic of Lara that goes viral, the sparkly girl goes out for revenge. She's going to hit Marnie where it hurts - the Mustangs.

episodes.name: Girl Crush
episodes.overview: Danny sacks Bella from the Mustangs after she messes up on the pitch. And to make matters worse, her dad says he's coming to watch her next game. How is she going to hide the fact that she's no longer even on the team?

episodes.name: OTP
episodes.overview: Lara tells Marnie that Gabe has a crush on her. But Marnie can't imagine kissing Gabe, or can she? Determined to move the budding romance forward, Lara organises a party.

episodes.name: Kick Like A Girl
episodes.overview: At a tournament, the Mustangs are thrashed by the Wildcats in the first round. Do they need a new captain to pull the team together? And can Anusha handle being second banana to Bella and her new found confidence?

episodes.name: Oh Em Gee
episodes.overview: Marnie's hunch about Ruby going to the Wildcats turns out to be right, so she and Liv organise a nachos night in an attempt to get her to stay. But will guacamole and corn chips be enough to keep their star player onside?

episodes.name: Flawless
episodes.overview: When Lara sucks up to the mansplaining Tom, Marnie gets mad. But when Lara dives like a diva and gets awarded a dodgy free kick, Marnie totally loses it. Doesn't Lara realise that there's more to life than being looked at?

episodes.name: RUOK?
episodes.overview: After a disappointing mark at school, Anusha throws herself into developing strategies for the team. But as her perfectionist friend unravels, Bella gets more and more concerned about Anusha.

episodes.name: The Feels
episodes.overview: After encouraging Nush's disastrous tactics, Marnie has to girl up to a hostile team and rally the troops - it's the semis this weekend so it's time to set differences aside and do some hardcore training, Mustangs style.

episodes.name: Slay
episodes.overview: The Mustangs have made it to the final but it feels like nobody at the club has faith in them and even the girls themselves start to have doubts. Can Marnie pull together a championship winning team?

episodes.name: Mustangs Forever
episodes.overview: The nail biting final is in play and the Mustangs and Wildcats are drawing 2-2. But when tensions rise pitch side - the game is called off and the Wildcats win on league points. But is this the end of the Mustangs story?

episodes.name: Wake Up Call
episodes.overview: Back together again for a new season, the Mustangs are confident and hungry for some silverware... But can they win without Ruby?

episodes.name: Shake Up Call
episodes.overview: The Mustangs need to get serious before the season officially starts - time for some unusual training methods, player recruitment, and a big shake up of the team's formation.

episodes.name: Get Real
episodes.overview: Marnie struggles to accept her new position in the team, while an injury forces Lara to face giving up dreams of gym glory.

episodes.name: The Doubt Worm
episodes.overview: Bella ends up in a spiral of self doubt after missing a goal - and everyone's opinions on how to help her only make it worse.

episodes.name: No Pressure
episodes.overview: The grudge match against the Wildcats has everyone feeling the pressure, especially Marnie, who develops some obsessive pre-game rituals.

episodes.name: Pity Party
episodes.overview: Marnie is forced to play friendship umpire when a team night watching soccer gets turned into a pity-party for heartbroken Liv, and Ruby's unexpected appearance divides the girls.

episodes.name: In Sync
episodes.overview: Marnie and the team campaign to get sanitary bins for the Mustangs clubhouse, while Anusha struggles to find the balance between independence and the support she needs.

episodes.name: You Do You
episodes.overview: Marnie has been keeping a secret from Liv and when it emerges, Liv questions whether soccer is really her passion.

episodes.name: Sparkly Girls
episodes.overview: Playing in a skills camp with the best in the league, Marnie gets a wake up call - she's going to have to work a lot harder for her dream than she'd realised.

episodes.name: Seven and Half Minutes
episodes.overview: Marnie desperately wants to get scouted but to do that, she has to persuade Anton to let her play with the boys. And miss half of the Mustangs crucial semi-final.

episodes.name: Step Up
episodes.overview: After spying the Wildcats bullying Ruby, Anusha gets carried away with a plan to take action. But Ruby stands up for herself.

episodes.name: Nailbiter
episodes.overview: The looming final against the Wildcats is sending everyone a bit crazy. Have the Mustangs got what it takes to finally win the trophy?

episodes.name: Hoof Five!
episodes.overview: The penalty shootouts are nail-bitingly close but even after the whistle blows and the final score is announced, there's still one last surprise in store for the Mustangs.

episodes.name: Hurly Burly
episodes.overview: The Mustangs-Wildcats merger means constant fighting in the new team. If they want to win, it's time to make some big changes.

episodes.name: Level Up
episodes.overview: A glimpse of Michaela's vulnerable side gives an unexpected perspective, and Marnie tries her hardest to keep up at State.

episodes.name: Obsessed
episodes.overview: Certain that Gabe likes Bella, Anusha plans an elaborate, project managed set up. But there's one major variable she did not account for.

episodes.name: Dress is More
episodes.overview: Zee's gone ball-hog on the pitch and nobody's impressed, while Marnie panics over mixing her new State friends with the Mustangs at her birthday party.

episodes.name: Roll With It
episodes.overview: Lara and Ruby are pushed into patching up their wobbly friendship, but they are stalled by some painful truth bombs.

episodes.name: We Stand
episodes.overview: It's Unity Day at the club, but the girls vs boys exhibition match is derailed by Tom's aggressive foul against TJ.

episodes.name: State Moves
episodes.overview: Marnie's relegated to the sidelines yet again at State, while Bella struggles with peoples assumptions about her — can't everyone just let her be?

episodes.name: C is For Complete
episodes.overview: The Mustangs have one last chance of making it into the finals, but despite captain Ruby's best efforts, they're struggling to step up.

episodes.name: Spikey Words
episodes.overview: Liv's attempt to lift Mustangs morale seriously backfires when she accidentally butt-dials Michaela while venting about the team.

episodes.name: The Crossroads
episodes.overview: Marnie tries to keep up at State with Ruby hot at her heels, and Anusha tries to become friends with Gabe.

episodes.name: I See You
episodes.overview: Ruby has to choose whether to pursue opportunities at State or aim for Team USA, while Marnie's knee injury has her in a deep funk.

episodes.name: In The Struggle, There's Joy
episodes.overview: Ruby makes a big announcement, and the Mustangs knuckle down ahead of the semis, but on game day, Danny's nowhere to be seen.

episodes.name: Mustangs Forever and Ever
episodes.overview: The Mustangs have to face whether the team has a future, and Lara realises she has something important to tell Ruby.
